  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>General Information:The Beverly Hills Plaza offers a garden oasis of tranquility. Whether your stay is short or long, the intimate size of the hotel and its hospitable staff enables the Plaza to deliver personalized service.  Location:The Beverly Hills Plaza Hotel is a unique all-suite hotel superbly located between exciting Westwood Village and the glamorous Rodeo Drive and Century City. Area:Stylish comfort within strolling distance to the best of Beverly Hills---Neiman Marcus, Saks and Barneys are among the favorites. Recreation:Le Petit Café offers a continental menu from breakfast to late supper, and service is also available in the garden, poolside or in your suite. The conference center provides a low-key and relaxing alternative to the big business hotels. Rooms:Beyond the intimate marble lobby, the 116 suites are tastefully decorated with modern, European-influenced décor; many have a clean, airy, almost Scandinavian feel. White-painted French doors open onto open-air walkways overlooking the pool and koi pond with waterfalls. Rooms include kitchenettes, marble bathrooms and private balconies with Jacuzzis.</Text>
  </Description>
